SIMPLE: resolvent
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Resolvent
<hw>Re*solv"ent</hw> <pr>(-<it>e</it>nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having
power to resolve; causing solution; solvent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resolvent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Resolvent
<hw>Re*solv"ent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>resolvens</ets>, p.
pr. of <ets>resolvere</ets>: cf. F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧solvant</ets>. See
<er>Resolve</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That which has the power of
resolving, or causing solution; a solvent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>That which has power to disperse
inflammatory or other tumors; a discutient; anything which aids the
absorption of effused products.</def> <rj><au>Coxe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>An equation upon whose solution
the solution of a given pproblem depends.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resolver</ent>⟦br⟧
